               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt; [[Carling, DThTA]] has “a1?” (with a question mark!) - do sides need to be swapped? (TI)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Translation [[Ogihara 2009]]: 417:&lt;br&gt;
a1 /// Four marrows of the flash made proper. ///&lt;br&gt;
a2 /// Medicine proper for (personal storage in) seven days. || Medicine which lasts for life. ///&lt;br&gt;
a3 /// Five medicines of root crops. ///&lt;br&gt;
a4 /// Five salts. ///&lt;br&gt;
a5 /// medicine which lasts for life ///&lt;br&gt;
b1 /// Here (is the) medicine that can be consumed ordinarily [as the meal of monks]. ///&lt;br&gt;
b2 /// It is not to be eaten. || Medicine that should not be preserved overnight. ///&lt;br&gt;
b3 /// ... as long as the time has not passed, it is to be consumed. ///&lt;br&gt;
b4 /// If the time has passed, it is not to be consumed. ///&lt;br&gt;
b5 /// ... it is to be consumed. In seven days, it is to be consumed. The time has passed ///
&lt;/p&gt;</item>
